The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 BCCI to wait and watch

Mumbai: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) has opted for a wait and watch policy over the formation of Indian Cricket League by Subhash Chandras Essel Group, which has roped in former captain Kapil Dev and ex-wicketkeeper Kiran More on its executive board. 

We dont know the details of what has been planned. So far the announcements have mentioned formation of six teams, but we are unsure whether its detrimental for Indian cricket and the BCCI, Board sources said on Tuesday. (PTI) 




